Vice President Kamala Harris expressed gratitude and appreciation for the work of leaders in a teleconference. She acknowledged the challenges faced during the pandemic, including the use of teleconferencing. Harris thanked the leaders for their partnership and highlighted the importance of their work in shaping the country. She emphasized the significance of the current moment in history and the actions being taken to demonstrate the character of the nation. Harris discussed the recent passage of the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law, which aims to improve infrastructure, create jobs, and provide affordable internet access. She also emphasized the administration's commitment to supporting unions and the importance of passing the Build Back Better Act to lower living costs and address the climate crisis. Harris called on the Senate to pass the act and expressed confidence in the positive impact it will have on the country. She concluded by expressing belief in the future of the United States and the importance of working together.